definition.value: An amino trisaccharide consisting of alpha-L-fucopyranose, beta-D-galactopyranose and 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-D-glucopyranose residues joined in sequence by (1->6) and (1->4) glycosidic bonds.
A beta-D-Glcp-(1->4)-D-Galp in which the carbon bearing the anomeric hydroxy group has alpha configuration.

A trisaccharide that is alpha-D-glucopyranosyl-(1->3)-D-galactopyranose in which the hydroxy group at position 4 of the D-galactopyranose moiety has been glycosylated by an alpha-L-fucopyranosyl group.
A Delta(4)-beta-D-GlcpA-(1->3)-D-GalpNAc4S in which the the carbon bearing the anomeric hydroxy group has beta- configuration.
A glycosyl glycoside that is alpha-D-galactopyranose in which the anomeric hydroxy group has been converted into the corresponding alpha-D-glucopyranosyl derivative.
An amino disaccharide that is beta-L-fucose in which the hydroxy group at position 3 has been converted into the corresponding 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranoside.
An amino trisaccharide consisting of two beta-D-galactopyranose residues and a 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-D-glucopyranose residue joined in sequence by (1->6) glycosidic bonds.

A branched amino nonasaccharide consisting of a linear sequence of N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl, beta-D-galactosyl, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl, beta-D-galactosyl and D-glucose residues linked sequentially (2->3), (1->3), (1->3) and (1->4), to the N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl residue is also linked (2->6) an N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl residue, while the galactosyl residue proximal to the reducing end has also linked (1->3) to it an alpha-L-fucosyl (1->3)-[beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)]-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl trisaccharide unit.
A trisaccharide consisting of two beta-D-galactopyranose residues and a beta-D-galactopyranose residue joined in sequence by two (1->6) glycosidic bonds.
A Delta(4)-beta-D-Glcp-(1->3)-D-GalpNAc6S in which the carbon bearing the anomeric hydroxy group has beta- configuration.
A trisaccharide consisting of an alpha-D-galactopyranose residue and two beta-D-glucopyranose residues joined in sequence by (1->2) and (1->4) glycosidic linkages.
A beta-D-Galp-(1->3)-alpha-D-Galp-(1->4)-D-Galp in which the anomeric hydroxy group has beta configuration

A glucotriose that is alpha-D-glucopyranosyl-(1->6)-alpha-D-glucopyranoside in which the anomeric hydroxy group has been converted into the corresponding alpha-D-glucopyranoside. An unusual trisaccharide abundant in the silverleaf whitefly, Bemisia argentifolii.
